  "prompt": "Which is the best haircut for man?",
  "response": "The best haircut for a man depends on several factors, including face shape, hair type, personal style, and lifestyle. Here are a few popular options to consider based on different criteria:\n\n1. **Face Shape:**\n   - **Oval:** Most styles work well, from a classic quiff to a buzz cut.\n   - **Round:** Opt for styles that add height, such as a pompadour or faux hawk.\n   - **Square:** Go for cuts that soften the angles, like textured layers or side-swept bangs.\n   - **Rectangle/Oblong:** Balance length with width using side parts or layered styles.\n   - **Heart:** Choose styles with volume around the temples, like a crew cut or textured quiff.\n\n2. **Hair Type:**\n   - **Straight Hair:** Slicked-back styles or undercuts can look sharp and clean.\n   - **Wavy Hair:** Embrace natural texture with a tousled or layered style.\n   - **Curly Hair:** Go for medium to long length to showcase curls, with an undercut for contrast.\n   - **Thick Hair:** A textured crop or fade can help manage volume.\n   - **Fine/Thin Hair:** Consider shorter styles like the buzz cut or textured crop to add fullness.\n\n3. **Lifestyle:**\n   - If you prefer low-maintenance styles, a buzz cut or crew cut requires minimal upkeep.\n   - For professional settings, a classic taper or side part looks polished and sophisticated.\n   - If you enjoy styling your hair, pompadours and long layers give you versatility.\n\nUltimately, the best haircut is one that makes you feel confident and suits your personal style. It's always a good idea to consult with a professional barber or stylist who can provide tailored advice based on your specific needs and preferences.",
